  "local_port": 53662,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I restore misc files from phone?",
  "response": "Restoring miscellaneous (misc) files from your phone can vary depending on the type of files, your device's operating system (Android or iOS), and whether you have backups available. Below are several methods you can use to attempt to recover and restore these files:\n\n### **For Android Devices**\n\n1. **Check Built-in Backups:**\n   - **Google Drive Backup:**\n     - Go to **Settings > Google > Backup** on your device.\n     - Check if your device was backed up recently.\n     - To restore, you might need to perform a factory reset and restore from the backup during the setup process.\n   \n2. **Use a File Recovery App:**\n   - **Note:** Most file recovery apps require root access.\n   - **DiskDigger:**\n     - Download and install [DiskDigger](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.defianttech.diskdigger&hl=en&gl=US) from the Google Play Store.\n     - Follow the in-app instructions to scan and recover deleted files.\n   - **EaseUS MobiSaver:**\n     - Install [EaseUS MobiSaver](https://www.easeus.com/android-data-recovery-software/free-android-data-recovery.html) on your computer.\n     - Connect your Android device via USB and follow the on-screen instructions.\n\n3. **Connect to a PC and Use Recovery Software:**\n   - **Steps:**\n     1. Connect your Android device to your PC using a USB cable.\n     2. Ensure that **USB Debugging** is enabled on your device (`Settings > Developer options > USB Debugging`).\n     3. Use trusted recovery software such as [Dr.Fone](https://drfone.wondershare.com/android-file-recovery.html) or [Recuva](https://www.ccleaner.com/recuva) to scan your device and recover files.\n\n4. **Check Cloud Services:**\n   - **Google Photos, Drive, or other cloud storage apps** might have backups of your misc files.\n   - Open each relevant app and check the trash or recently deleted sections.\n\n### **For iOS Devices**\n\n1. **Restore from iCloud Backup:**\n   - **Steps:**\n     1. Go to **Settings > General > Reset** on your iPhone.\n     2. Select **Erase All Content and Settings**.\n     3. After the device resets, choose to **Restore from iCloud Backup** during setup.\n     4. Select the backup that likely contains your misc files.\n\n2. **Restore from iTunes/Finder Backup:**\n   - **Steps:**\n     1. Connect your iPhone to the computer you normally sync with.\n     2. Open **iTunes** (on Windows or older macOS) or **Finder** (on macOS Catalina and later).\n     3. Select your device and choose **Restore Backup**.\n     4. Pick the most relevant backup to restore your files.\n\n3. **Use Third-Party Recovery Software:**\n   - Tools like [Dr.Fone](https://drfone.wondershare.com/), [iMobie PhoneRescue](https://www.imobie.com/phonerescue/), or [Tenorshare UltData](https://www.tenorshare.com/products/iphone-data-recovery.html) can help recover deleted files directly from your device or backups.\n   - **Note:** These tools often require purchase for full functionality and might have limitations based on iOS versions.\n\n4. **Check Recently Deleted Albums:**\n   - For photos and videos, open the **Photos** app.\n   - Go to **Albums > Recently Deleted**.\n   - Select the files you want to recover and tap **Recover**.\n\n### **General Tips**\n\n- **Act Quickly:** The sooner you attempt recovery after the files are deleted, the higher the chances of successful restoration. Continued use of the device can overwrite the deleted data.\n  \n- **Enable Future Backups:**\n  - Regularly back up your device to prevent future data loss.\n  - Use cloud services or local backups via PC/Mac.\n\n- **Avoid Rooting or Jailbreaking Unless Necessary:** While rooting (Android) or jailbreaking (iOS) can grant more access for recovery, it may void warranties and pose security risks.\n\n- **Consult Professional Services:** If the files are extremely important and cannot be recovered through software, consider reaching out to professional data recovery services, though they can be costly.\n\n### **Preventative Measures for the Future**\n\n- **Use Cloud Storage:**\n  - Utilize services like Google Drive, Dropbox, OneDrive, or iCloud to automatically back up important files.\n  \n- **Regular Backups:**\n  - Schedule regular backups to your computer or an external storage device.\n\n- **File Management Practices:**\n  - Organize files systematically to make backups easier and reduce the risk of accidental deletion.\n\nIf you provide more specific details about the type of files you're trying to restore and your device's operating system, I can offer more targeted advice.",
